                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d188">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.515/11–1444: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-14T14:00:00+03:00"
                            >November 14, 1944—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 14—1:52 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4364. ReEmbs 3997, October 20, 11 a.m.<note n="54" xml:id="d188fn54">Not printed;
                        in this telegram the Chargé” reported that the Soviet Foreign Office had not
                        replied to his note of September 30 regarding Resolution VI
                        (800.515/10–2044).</note> The Embassy received this morning a note from the
                    Foreign Office dated November 12 stating that the Chiefs of the Soviet Missions
                    in Stockholm and Ankara have been instructed to present notes on the subject of
                    Resolution VI of the Bretton Woods Conference but that in view of the fact that
                    the Soviet Government has no diplomatic missions in Dublin, Madrid, Lisbon,
                    Tangier and Bern, the Foreign Office is unable to transmit similar notes to the
                    appropriate governments.</p>
                <p>No date is given as to when the instructions were issued to present the notes to
                    the Swedish and Turkish Governments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
